{
  "stem": "14613.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They gave us some clothes, which of course, did not fit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and we were sent- When I say Auschwitz, it is really incorrect, because we really went to Birkenau, likely, which was the-- which was the large camp for all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Auschwitz, itself, was a small camp, but-- where only small part of the people were sent to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know, 90%-95% of us went to-- to Birkenau, which was a camp next to Auschwitz, a few miles away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we have found ourselves in a camp, in this Auschwitz-Birkenau, which somehow was called the Zigeunerlager, the gypsy camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this was a camp that-- contrary to many other small parts in Auschwitz or in Birkenau-- where the people were sent basically for annihilation.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not for work, not for anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they called it the gypsy camp, I found out later, because in this particular camp, some time ago, they sent all the gypsies, and they killed them.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the name became the gypsy camp, the Zigeuner camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's where I spent-- and I was sent with my brother there to this gypsy camp in Auschwitz-Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] What-- what can you say about this Birkenau?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you go there today, you can see, as far as your eye can see, chimneys.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every few meters, you see a chimney.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But during the time I was there, each chimney represented maybe 1,500 to 2,000 people in a barrack, wooden barrack.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was not much place to sleep.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were some bunk beds, like a--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But there were four, five, six people laying together in one space.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
